  "title": "Kubernetes Administrator (L2/L3 – EKS)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>We are seeking an experienced <strong>Operations Engineer / Kubernetes Administrator (L2/L3)</strong> to support, monitor, and operate an existing <strong>AWS EKS platform</strong> across cloud and on-prem environments. The role focuses on platform operations, stability, and advanced troubleshooting of Kubernetes-based systems.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Provide <strong>L2/L3 operational support</strong> for AWS EKS clusters</p></li><li><p>Monitor, maintain, and optimize Kubernetes environments (cloud/on-prem)</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot container, cluster, and infrastructure issues</p></li><li><p>Perform cluster upgrades, patching, scaling, and performance tuning</p></li><li><p>Manage monitoring, alerting, incident response, and root cause analysis</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with DevOps and application teams to ensure platform reliability and security</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Hands-on experience with <strong>Kubernetes administration (EKS)</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong background in <strong>production operations and support (L2/L3)</strong></p></li><li><p>Experience with monitoring and observability tools</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of cloud infrastructure and container ecosystems</p></li><li><p>Scripting and automation skills are an advantage</p></li></ul><p>#Kubernetes #EKS </p>",
